-- Global Funds Sell Net 51.3 Million Rupees of Indian Derivatives
-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 2012-07-27T03:30:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-27/global-funds-sell-net-51-3-million-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors  sold a  net 51.3
million rupees ($923,492 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, declined 33.6 percent to 619.75 billion rupees on
the last day of trading in contracts for July, according to the
exchangeâ€™s  website . Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds sold a net 11.8 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
